# Required. A GitHub Personal Access Token, used to read PUBLIC data only
# (profiles, repos, contributors, contributions). No special scopes needed —
# a classic PAT with zero scopes checked, or a fine-grained token with no
# repository/account permissions granted, both work fine.
#
# Why it's required even for public data: unauthenticated GitHub API requests
# are capped at 60/hour, which one cold profile or squad lookup can burn
# through alone (see docs/caching-and-rate-limits.md). An authenticated token
# raises that to 5,000/hour (GraphQL is billed in points against the same
# budget, not a flat per-request count).
#
# Create one at https://github.com/settings/tokens -> "Generate new token
# (classic)" -> no scopes -> Generate.
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional. Used only by npm run dev / npm start to know which port
# getSiteUrl() (lib/site-url.ts) should point local links at. Defaults to
# 3000 if unset — you only need this if you run the dev server on a
# different port.
# PORT=3000
